===CoffeeInfo===
# speaker:Narrator # portrait:portrait1 # layout:right
Coffee in Ottoman life was more than a drink, it was a ritual of friendship and thought. 
Brewed thick and strong in a small pot called a <i>cezve</i>, which invites conversation.
In the coffee houses of Istanbul, people of all classes and faiths gathered to share ideas, news, and poetry, turning each cup into a moment of connection and respect.

